2026-05-14 | Check if Array is a Good Array

	Question
Return true if nums is a good array.
	Approach
1.	Let:
		n = nums.size() - 1  
2.	Sort the array  
3.	Check:
		nums[0..n-2] == 1..n-1  
4.	Check:
		last two elements are both n  
5.	If all conditions hold:
		return true
	else:
		return false  
	Time Complexity
	O(n log n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1) extra
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool isGood(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size() - 1;
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        for(int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++){
            if(nums[i] != i + 1)
                return false;
        }
        return nums[n - 1] == n &&
               nums[n] == n;
    }
};
	Key Insight
After sorting:
		a good array must exactly look like:
				[1,2,3,...,n,n]
So validation becomes very straightforward.
